isoiec80000:term-t7-6.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "L_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(L)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-6.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-6.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-6.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of radiant intensity with respect to projected area in a specified direction at a specified point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"e\" = (\"d\"l_\"e\")/(\"d\"A) 1/(\"cos\"alpha)
++++

where stem:[I_\"e\"] is radiant intensity (<<t7-5.1>>), A is area (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[alpha] is the angle between the normal to the surface at the specified point and the specified direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """See also <<cls-0.1>>.

For Planckian radiation,

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"e\" = sigma/pi T^4
++++

where stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<iso80000-5>>) and stem:[sigma] is the Stefan-Boltzmann constant (<<iso80000-1>>).

The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminance\" (<<t7-15>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon radiance\" (<<t7-22>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/(sr*m^2) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*s^(-3)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .